- AUC (Area Under the Curve) is a metric used to evaluate the performance of binary classification models; a higher AUC indicates better performance;
- Precision is the ratio of true positive predictions to the total positive predictions; a higher precision indicates fewer false positives;
- Recall is the ratio of true positive predictions to the total actual positives; a higher recall indicates fewer false negatives;
- 'Top Performer' refers to models that are ranked 1 in either AUC, precision, or recall within their category.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(audit_id) 
FROM model_audits 
WHERE rating < (SELECT AVG(rating) FROM model_audits);

SELECT category_name
FROM model_categories
WHERE category_id = 1;

